##Plato

data <- phi%>% 
  filter(author=="Plato")
dim(data)
## [1] 38366    11
#View(data)

#1. Switch to lower case 2. Remove numbers 3. Remove punctuation marks and stopwords 4. Remove extra whitespaces
data_corpus = Corpus(VectorSource(data$sentence_lowered))
data_corpus = tm_map(data_corpus, removeNumbers)
## Warning in tm_map.SimpleCorpus(data_corpus, removeNumbers): transformation drops
## documents
data_corpus = tm_map(data_corpus, removePunctuation)
## Warning in tm_map.SimpleCorpus(data_corpus, removePunctuation): transformation
## drops documents
data_corpus = tm_map(data_corpus, removeWords, c("the", "and", stopwords("english")))
## Warning in tm_map.SimpleCorpus(data_corpus, removeWords, c("the", "and", :
## transformation drops documents
data_corpus =  tm_map(data_corpus, stripWhitespace)
## Warning in tm_map.SimpleCorpus(data_corpus, stripWhitespace): transformation
## drops documents
inspect(data_corpus[1])
## <<SimpleCorpus>>
## Metadata:  corpus specific: 1, document level (indexed): 0
## Content:  documents: 1
## 
## [1] whats new socrates make leave usual haunts lyceum spend time king archons court
data_dtm <- DocumentTermMatrix(data_corpus)




#To reduce the dimension of the DTM, we can remove the less frequent terms such that the sparsity is less than 0.95
data_dtm = removeSparseTerms(data_dtm, 0.99)

data_dtm
## <<DocumentTermMatrix (documents: 38366, terms: 146)>>
## Non-/sparse entries: 118806/5482630
## Sparsity           : 98%
## Maximal term length: 10
## Weighting          : term frequency (tf)
findFreqTerms(data_dtm, 1000)
##  [1] "make"      "socrates"  "time"      "say"       "must"      "know"     
##  [7] "dont"      "one"       "think"     "man"       "thing"     "men"      
## [13] "first"     "good"      "just"      "others"    "right"     "way"      
## [19] "will"      "things"    "like"      "even"      "people"    "now"      
## [25] "well"      "can"       "said"      "many"      "two"       "also"     
## [31] "something" "see"       "soul"
freq = data.frame(sort(colSums(as.matrix(data_dtm)), decreasing=TRUE))
wordcloud(rownames(freq), freq[,1], max.words=50, colors=brewer.pal(1, "Dark2"))
